The paper is about using deep neural networks for salient object detection in complex images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel framework that utilizes low-level features to improve the performance of the network, which involves designing the network architecture and joint discriminative learning, both of which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using hinge-loss SVM detector, which is a machine learning algorithm (cs.LG). The paper involves training the network to learn the saliency score of each region within the bounding box, which is a task related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on benchmark datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
